======================================================================
SUMMARY
======================================================================
  p=7:  corrected sign law FAILS
  p=11: corrected sign law FAILS
  p=19: corrected sign law 24/36

  Key insight: sign(h_hat[a,b]) = chi(q) * chi(ab)
  where q is the minimum resonance (q*a = +/-b mod p)
  This SUBSUMES the product law (which assumed chi(q)=+1)
  and EXPLAINS the failures at p=19 (where chi(3)=-1, chi(7)=+1, etc.)

  Connection to THM-155:
  The sign law controls how c5 and ov2 Walsh coefficients cancel
  to make c5+2*ov2 constant. The resonance structure is the algebraic
  reason behind the constancy of the disjoint 3-cycle identity.
